It’s not every day we get to chat with one of the 100 most influential people in the world and an actress ranked ninth in the New York Times’s '25 Greatest Actors of the 21st Century'. Tanya Nefdt spoke to her about her latest film that's set to premiere on Netflix next week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Viola Davis is a force to be reckoned with in the movie industry. She is the first African-American actress to achieve the Triple Crown of Acting. These are the three highest accolades possible in the movie industry - an Oscar, an Emmy, and two Tonys. READ: Netflix announces second season of local hit series 'Blood & Water' Viola proves time after time that she can play any part, like Netflix’s latest offering, Ma Rainey’s Black Bottom. Set in the 1920s, the movie sees Viola taking on the big character of Ma Rainey - known as 'The Mother of the Blues'. The film is produced by Denzel Washington. Ma Rainey’s Black Bottom is expected to premiere on Netflix next week.